		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I tried to think a little bit about it and here my extra comments:
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">B00daW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- Setting up times for multiple people to be in the channel to discuss certain dev-related topics.</div><br /><br />You will have to always create a post for the next discussion. This seems more something that you would put as news on the front page of the nesdev site or on the wiki in the community section.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">B00daW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- Advertising the channel as a way for instantaneous help or aid.</div><br /><br />Unless you read that specific forum, there will be no advertisement. Same thing as previous comment, should be on the front page of nesdev or wiki is again a better solution.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">B00daW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- Listing future and present bot-related commands.</div><br /><br />You need sticky just for that. Hmm.. In that case, it could always be fine. It could be added to the wiki too.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">B00daW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- Basic communication between the channel and the forum.</div>
<br />
<br />In that case to discuss about what you said in the channel, I have no problem with it. That make sense and we can open it.
<br />
<br />In brief, if you want to continue to discuss what was in the channel then I have no objection against that. As for the promotion, you should try to promote it on the main page and wiki to reach more audience. Other website could be a possibility too.

		

