	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />EFnet #nesdev has been around for years.  A lot of people left it after it became sort of a cesspool for nonsense.  A year or so has passed since then and we're back on topic and have many users interested in NESdevving and related conversation.  Competant developers and users, without dropping too many names, engage in intellectual conversation on a daily or nightly basis.  The channel really is a resource to the public.
<br />
<br />Personally as an op, I think the only rule #nesdev has is:  Dev related conversations trump all conversations.  Otherwise almost anything goes.
<br />
<br />I really see no reason not to link the forums and the channel.  However, majority (+ admin) rules.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


